cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.MM, cs.CE 

This paper deals with interference networks and coding schemes, which are typically studied in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The use of multiple-antenna transmitters/receivers and linear combinations of information messages also suggests the sub-categories of Signal Processing (cs.SI) and Multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the mention of cognitive interference channels and coordination points towards the sub-category of Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science (cs.CE).
